SENATE BILL 657
F2 6lr2713
CF HB 919
By: Senator Henson
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Maryland Higher Education Commission – Practical Applications of Real Estate
3 Appraisal (PAREA) Grant Program – Established
4 FOR the purpose of establishing the Practical Applications of Real Estate Appraisal
5 (PAREA) Grant Program to provide grants to certain individuals with the goal of
6 becoming a real estate appraiser in certain communities; requiring the Maryland
7 Higher Education Commission to administer the Program; and generally relating to
8 the Practical Applications of Real Estate Appraisal (PAREA) Grant Program.
9 BY adding to
10 Article – Education
11 Section 18–4201 and 18–4202 to be under the new subtitle “Subtitle 42. PAREA
12 Grant Program”
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – Education
18 SUBTITLE 42. PAREA GRANT PROGRAM.
19 18–4201.
20 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
21 INDICATED.
22 (B) “PAREA” MEANS THE PRACTICAL APPLICATIONS OF REAL ESTATE
23 APPRAISAL.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *sb0657*

2 SENATE BILL 657
1 (C) “PROGRAM” MEANS THE PRACTICAL APPLICATIONS OF REAL ESTATE
2 APPRAISAL GRANT PROGRAM.
3 18–4202.
4 (A) THERE IS A PRACTICAL APPLICATIONS OF REAL ESTATE APPRAISAL
5 GRANT PROGRAM IN THE COMMISSION.
6 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO:
7 (1) ASSIST IN CLOSING APPRAISAL GAPS THAT OCCUR IN
8 HISTORICALLY REDLINED NEIGHBORHOODS AND UNDERREPRESENTED
9 COMMUNITIES;
10 (2) AWARD GRANTS TO MINORITIES WHO RESIDE IN HISTORICALLY
11 REDLINED NEIGHBORHOODS AND UNDERREPRESENTED COMMUNITIES WITH THE
12 GOAL OF PURSUING PAREA; AND
13 (3) DIVERSIFY THE APPRAISAL FIELD.
14 (C) THE COMMISSION SHALL ADMINISTER THE PROGRAM.
15 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
16 1, 2026.

